NAME

      gcloud preview managed-instance-groups create - insert (Create) a managed
         instance group

SYNOPSIS

      gcloud preview managed-instance-groups create GROUP
         [--api-version API_VERSION; default="v1beta2"]
         --base-instance-name BASE_INSTANCE_NAME [--description DESCRIPTION]
         [--format FORMAT] [--help] [--project PROJECT] [--quiet, -q]
         --size SIZE [--target-pool [TARGET_POOL ...]] --template TEMPLATE [-h]

DESCRIPTION

      Insert (Create) a managed instance group.

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS

      GROUP

         Managed instance group name.

FLAGS

      --base-instance-name BASE_INSTANCE_NAME

         The base name to use for the Compute Engine instances that will be
         created in the managed instance group.

      --description DESCRIPTION

         Managed instance group description.

      --size SIZE

         Initial number of instances in the managed instance group.

      --target-pool [TARGET_POOL ...]

         Compute Engine Target Pools to add the instances to. Target Pools must
         be specified by name, not by URL. Example: --target-pools
         "target-pool-1 target-pool-2"

      --template TEMPLATE

         Name of the Compute Engine instance template resource to be used.

GLOBAL FLAGS

      --api-version API_VERSION; default="v1beta2"

         Optional API version.

      --format FORMAT

         Specify a format for printed output. By default, a command-specific
         human-friendly output format is used. Setting this flag to one of the
         available options will serialize the result of the command in the
         chosen format and print it to stdout. Supported formats are: json,
         text, yaml.

      --help

         Display detailed help.

      --project PROJECT

         The Google Cloud Platform project name to use for this invocation. If
         omitted then the current project is assumed.

      --quiet, -q

         Disable all interactive prompts when running gcloud commands. If input
         is required, defaults will be used, or an error will be raised.

      -h

         Print a summary help and exit.

NOTES

      This command is in the Google Cloud SDK preview component. See installing
      components if it is not installed.

